Official Wellspring Boys Soccer try-outs will begin next week Wed. August 12 -14, 2020 at the Wellspring Soccer field 5pm -7pm.
Please make sure you have the following with you for try-outs:
1. Water, we will not have access to the school so bring plenty.
2. Shoes, shinguards and a mask.
3. A valid physical or you may transfer your physical from your previous school if you are a new Wellspring student. If you had a valid physical on file in our office last year, you do NOT need to get another for this year.
4. A ready to play attitude. We will have both a JV and Varsity Team this year so if you've been thinking of playing...come try-out!
See you all there
Coach Russell

Wellspring Prep families, thank you for your continued patience as we work to develop a plan of what next steps need to take place to best serve our students over the next few weeks.

We understand that there are many questions/concerns that you may have, so please be sure that you are checking your emails for updates from us. As we receive new information, we will adjust our protocol accordingly.

If any of you did NOT receive our call or email regarding school closing, please email Ms. Moore (wmoore@wellspringprep.com), so that we can ensure we have your up-to-date phone number and email address added to our School Messenger system.

Any students that need to collect personal belongings, or school materials, will be allowed to enter the building between 8:00 am and 11:00 am on Monday, March 16th. Students will be required to check in and out through the main office. Students will have no more than five minutes to get what they need from their lockers and then must exit the building.

Please see the attached image for the full communication sent out this afternoon.

post_text: We’re doing some awesome things in AP Statistics. We did an investigation to determine the true average difference in the number of chocolate chips between name brand cookies and generic cookies. We constructed a confidence interval to analyze our results and determined that there isn't actually a difference between the number of chocolate chips in name brand versus generic. We do activities like this all the time in AP Statistics, students should talk to Ms. Fitzgerald if they are interested to learn more about this course!

Friendly reminder that tomorrow our students will be taking the PSAT and SAT exams. All 9th through 11th grade students need to be in school NO LATER than 7:30AM.

9th & 10th Grades - Dismissed at approximately 12:00PM
11th Grade - Dismissed at approximately 1:00PM
12th Grade - Dismissed at approximately 12:00PM

Seniors will have time to work with the Senior Advisors on college applications, scholarship applications, senior projects, AP course work, online courses, missing assignments, etc. in a designated area of the building. If they will be absent for the day, a parent/guardian needs to call the office to excuse them.

NOTE: Students with accommodations may have later dismissal times or may test at a later date.

Friendly reminder that parent-teacher conferences will be taking place today from 3:00-5:00PM, tomorrow (Thursday) from 1:00-8:00PM and Friday morning from 9:00AM-12:00PM. Conferences are by appointment only, but there is still space available. Please call the main office if you need assistance signing up for conferences.

There are two events happening during conferences:

(1) BOOK SALE - We have partnered with Schuler Books, who will give a percentage of sales to the PTO! Come to room #222 during conferences, or go to www.schulerbooks.com and enter the coupon code: wellspring (This code is valid Tuesday, March 26th through Friday, March 29th).

(2) NHS BAKE SALE - Do you need a pick me up to get you through your conferences? We have a remedy for you! NHS is having a bake sale during conferences this week! You can eat a yummy snack, grab a refreshing soda, and support your wolves! The bake sale will be going on during conferences on Wednesday, Thursday, and Friday! See you there parents!

Friendly reminder, our information meeting about our new Early College Program will take place tomorrow, February 21st at 6:30PM at Wellspring Prep. This program would provide the opportunity for WSP students to earn their high school diploma and up to an associate degree (or 60+ credit hours) through Davenport University.

An alternative meeting date is being provided today, February 20th at 6:30PM at Grand River Prep.

Parent attendance at the information meeting is required for students to be able to apply.

post_text:
Next week we are celebrating Spirit Week leading up to our Friday pep assembly and Saturday's Winter Formal!

Spirit Week Themes!
MONDAY: Sports Team Day
TUESDAY: Cartoon Character Day
WEDNESDAY: Career Day
THURSDAY: Superhero v. Villain Day
FRIDAY: Red/Pink Out

Spirit Week Dress Code:
No Masks, hats, sunglasses, or dyed hair.

If you are not participating in the Spirit Week theme, come in regular dress code!

Winter Formal: Hearts and Roses
WHEN: February 16th, 6-9:30pm

TICKETS: $10/1 ticket OR $15/2 tickets (sold at lunch this week); AT THE DOOR: $20

If you plan on bringing a guest from another school, they must be 20 or younger and guest forms must be completed and turned in by Thursday, February 14th at 8:00 AM. Forms can be found in the office or as you purchase tickets.

Dance Dress Code:
No plunging necklines, no slits that extend more than four inches above the knee, no bare stomachs and no dresses with cut-out designs anywhere. Stilettos are not allowed on the gym floor. No baggy pants, athletic wear, tennis shoes, or jeans.

We have a great opportunity for students to wrap up the semester on a positive note and prepare for semester exams this week. All teachers will be offering tutoring after school Monday through Thursday from 2:45PM - 3:45PM. These tutoring sessions will be a focused opportunity for students to make-up missing assessments or possibly take additional assessments (at teacher discretion) to raise their semester grade prior to exams.

Please feel free to reach out Mr. Lanaghan or Mrs. Hurrell if you have any questions regarding this opportunity.
